result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) and Operating w/PAC >= .02 Under IID Order (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) and the other charge, Operating w/PAC >= .02 Under IID Order (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Enrique Aranda was found guilty of Stalking, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.32(2).
  • Enrique Aranda was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Enrique Aranda was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.
